Summary: Perhaps the first UFO Sighting on Mars from the rover opportunity
divs: sighting detailsi was on the jpls web site the other night scanning through some of the photos that the rover opportunity had sent down. one of the photos from sol:869 caught my attention. i pulled the photo back to my pc and brought it up in photo shop. i looked closer and i was completely astonished at what i was looking at. i saw an object along the horizon that did not appear to be dust on the lens. i have worked with photo equipment for some time to know what dust looks like. so i use the magnifying glass in photo shop to pull the image in closer. if this was dust it would have become distorted and indistinguishable to the naked eye. this object kept its shape and clarity which told me it was at a distance from the rover at an altitude above the ground. as i looked closer at the photo i noticed the lighting it was coming from the right side of the photo and some objects on the group were casting shadows to the left. when i looked at the object in question closer i could see light hitting it from the right and a shadow being cast to its left. now i realize this is not an earth bound report and perhaps one of the first interplanetary reports sent in. i simply did not know who to contact! i sent jpl a copy of the photo with questions two weeks ago and have yet to hear back from them. i thought mufon would be interested in look at this and give me your thoughts on this. thank you. greg blackwell here is the url for the photo at jpl. http:\\marsrovers.jpl.nasa.gov\gallery\all\1\n\869\1n205336711eff73u6p1948l0m1.html i will also send the photo i have that i was looking at.
